MAGDELINE and her neighbour had been living next to each other for five years and she thought they were friends.But now the neighbour has disappeared and Magdeline&rsquo;s six-month-old boy, Luyanda, is also missing.Magdeline Mosele (37) said she was sitting with her neighbour, whom she knows only as India, in their flat in Marshall Street, Jeppestown in the Joburg CBD on 9 November. India picked up the child and took him to her room. Magdeline told Daily Sun: &ldquo;I went to the toilet, and when I came back I found my neighbour&rsquo;s room locked.&ldquo;I wasn&rsquo;t worried because India often used to take Luyanda out. When she didn&rsquo;t come back I went to look for her, but I couldn&rsquo;t find her. &ldquo;I went back to India&rsquo;s room and her boyfriend was there. He said he hadn&rsquo;t seen her either. We both went looking for India and my baby but couldn&rsquo;t find them. I had known and trusted the woman but now she&rsquo;s gone with my baby.&rdquo; India is a tall Indian woman, allegedly from Durban. She has burn marks on her face. At the time she was wearing a pink top with grey trousers and a white scarf.Magdeline said her baby was wearing blue clothing and he is light in complexion.Police spokesman Captain Richard Munyai said: &ldquo;We are appealing to anyone who might have information to come forward.&rdquo;People can call Detective-Constable Queen Modjadji on 079 879 5518 or 011 407 1600.